-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY
                CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END ASC,
                return_date ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_returns.sql
-- Join order_items with products, categories, and returns
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        p.name AS product_name,
        p.category_id,
        c.name AS category_name,
        r.return_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    order_id,
    product_id,
    quantity,
    product_name,
    category_id,
    category_name,
    return_id
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/mart/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
-- Calculate return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
        COUNT(return_id) AS total_items_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }}
    GROUP BY COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)')
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    CASE
        WHEN total_items_sold > 0 THEN
            CAST(total_items_returned AS DECIMAL(10,2)) / CAST(total_items_sold AS DECIMAL(10,2))
        ELSE 0
    END AS return_rate
FROM source
